ReportText: Chest, 2 views. History: Shortness of breath. Comparison: Chest radiograph dated 06/27/2013. Findings: PA and lateral views of the chest were obtained. The lungs are well expanded and clear. There is no focal consolidation, pleural effusions or pneumothoraces. The heart is normal in size and the aorta is unremarkable. There are no acute osseous abnormalities. Impression: Normal chest. The films and dictation have been reviewed with the Resident and I agree with the findings.
